<doc id="884059" wikidata="Q6637056" url="?curid=884059" title="List of rulers of Mombasa">
<text>Before 1502, the East African city of Mombasa was part of the Kilwa Sultanate. The independent Mombasa sultanate named &quot;Mvita&quot; (Swahili) or &quot;Manbasa&quot; (Arabic) was then established but was conquered by the Portuguese Empire during the 16th century. After this control alternated between the Portuguese and the Sultanate of Oman,before the establishment of the British East Africa Protectorate in 1887. Mombasa became part of independent Kenya in 1963.

